# Version Control Rules

## Commit Messages

- All commit messages MUST be written in English
- Follow the conventional commits specification:
  - Format: `type(scope): message`
  - Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore
  - Example: `feat(auth): add login with Google`
- Keep commits atomic and focused
- Write clear and descriptive messages
- Include relevant ticket numbers when applicable
- Add emojis to express emotions

## Pull Requests

- All PR titles and descriptions MUST be written in English
- PR title should be clear and descriptive
- PR description should include:
  - Purpose of the changes
  - Summary of main modifications
  - Testing performed
  - Screenshots for UI changes
  - Breaking changes if any
- Link related issues or tickets
- Keep PRs focused and reasonably sized

## Branch Management

- Use feature branches for development
- Keep branches up to date with main
- Delete branches after merging
- Use meaningful branch names in English
  - Format: `type/description`
  - Example: `feature/google-auth`

## Code Review

- Review comments should be in English
- Be constructive and specific
- Focus on:
  - Code quality
  - Test coverage
  - Documentation
  - Performance implications
  - Security considerations